<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
The call strcmp(shmem->name, name) can read beyond the bounds of the objects pointed to if either operand is NULL or not NUL-terminated. In the shown code there is no prior check that the parameter name is non-NULL (or that shmem->name is properly NUL-terminated), so passing name == NULL (or a non-terminated shmem->name due to earlier incorrect initialization) would cause strcmp to access out-of-bounds memory. This violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 21.17.
</scenario>

